{
  "video_id": "tz9-N_mRI04",
  "title": "This computer is learning to read your mind | DIY Neuroscience, a TED series",
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 0.0,
      "end_time": 7000.0,
      "text": "Translator: Joseph Geni Reviewer: Krystian Aparta"
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 12203.0,
      "end_time": 15620.0,
      "text": "Greg Gage: Mind-reading. You&#39;ve seen this in sci-fi movies:"
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 15860.0,
      "end_time": 16943.0,
      "text": "machines that can read our thoughts."
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 16967.0,
      "end_time": 18765.0,
      "text": "However, there are devices today"
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 18789.0,
      "end_time": 21313.0,
      "text": "that can read the electrical activity from our brains."
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 21337.0,
      "end_time": 22609.0,
      "text": "We call this the EEG."
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 23695.0,
      "end_time": 26524.0,
      "text": "Is there information contained in these brainwaves?"
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 26548.0,
      "end_time": 29360.0,
      "text": "And if so, could we train a computer to read our thoughts?"
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 29385.0,
      "end_time": 32289.0,
      "text": "My buddy Nathan has been working to hack the EEG"
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 32313.000000000004,
      "end_time": 33989.0,
      "text": "to build a mind-reading machine."
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 34130.0,
      "end_time": 36470.0,
      "text": "[DIY Neuroscience]"
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 36939.0,
      "end_time": 38500.0,
      "text": "So this is how the EEG works."
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 38524.0,
      "end_time": 40368.0,
      "text": "Inside your head is a brain,"
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 40392.0,
      "end_time": 42950.0,
      "text": "and that brain is made out of billions of neurons."
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 42974.0,
      "end_time": 45980.0,
      "text": "Each of those neurons sends an electrical message to each other."
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 46500.0,
      "end_time": 48819.0,
      "text": "These small messages can combine to make an electrical wave"
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 48843.0,
      "end_time": 50413.0,
      "text": "that we can detect on a monitor."
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 50437.0,
      "end_time": 53161.0,
      "text": "Now traditionally, the EEG can tell us large-scale things,"
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 53185.0,
      "end_time": 55535.0,
      "text": "for example if you&#39;re asleep or if you&#39;re alert."
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 55559.0,
      "end_time": 57153.0,
      "text": "But can it tell us anything else?"
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 57177.0,
      "end_time": 58879.0,
      "text": "Can it actually read our thoughts?"
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 58903.0,
      "end_time": 60122.0,
      "text": "We&#39;re going to test this,"
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 60146.0,
      "end_time": 62769.0,
      "text": "and we&#39;re not going to start with some complex thoughts."
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 62793.0,
      "end_time": 64769.0,
      "text": "We&#39;re going to do something very simple."
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 64794.0,
      "end_time": 68470.0,
      "text": "Can we interpret what someone is seeing using only their brainwaves?"
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 68710.0,
      "end_time": 71710.0,
      "text": "Nathan&#39;s going to begin by placing electrodes on Christy&#39;s head."
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 71950.0,
      "end_time": 72618.0,
      "text": "Nathan: My life is tangled."
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 72642.0,
      "end_time": 73792.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 74152.0,
      "end_time": 76736.0,
      "text": "GG: And then he&#39;s going to show her a bunch of pictures"
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 76760.0,
      "end_time": 78281.0,
      "text": "from four different categories."
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 78305.0,
      "end_time": 80959.0,
      "text": "Nathan: Face, house, scenery and weird pictures."
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 80983.0,
      "end_time": 83481.0,
      "text": "GG: As we show Christy hundreds of these images,"
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 83505.0,
      "end_time": 87480.0,
      "text": "we are also capturing the electrical waves onto Nathan&#39;s computer."
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 87720.0,
      "end_time": 90458.0,
      "text": "We want to see if we can detect any visual information about the photos"
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 90482.0,
      "end_time": 91834.0,
      "text": "contained in the brainwaves,"
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 91858.0,
      "end_time": 94189.0,
      "text": "so when we&#39;re done, we&#39;re going to see if the EEG"
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 94213.0,
      "end_time": 96811.0,
      "text": "can tell us what kind of picture Christy is looking at,"
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 96835.0,
      "end_time": 100419.0,
      "text": "and if it does, each category should trigger a different brain signal."
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 100443.0,
      "end_time": 103710.0,
      "text": "OK, so we collected all the raw EEG data,"
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 103950.0,
      "end_time": 104245.0,
      "text": "and this is what we got."
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 105389.0,
      "end_time": 108327.0,
      "text": "It all looks pretty messy, so let&#39;s arrange them by picture."
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 108826.0,
      "end_time": 111482.0,
      "text": "Now, still a bit too noisy to see any differences,"
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 111506.0,
      "end_time": 114546.0,
      "text": "but if we average the EEG across all image types"
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 114570.0,
      "end_time": 117600.0,
      "text": "by aligning them to when the image first appeared,"
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 117300.0,
      "end_time": 118647.0,
      "text": "we can remove this noise,"
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 118671.0,
      "end_time": 121500.0,
      "text": "and pretty soon, we can see some dominant patterns"
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 121290.0,
      "end_time": 122592.0,
      "text": "emerge for each category."
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 122617.0,
      "end_time": 124773.0,
      "text": "Now the signals all still look pretty similar."
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 124797.0,
      "end_time": 126120.0,
      "text": "Let&#39;s take a closer look."
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 126360.0,
      "end_time": 128561.0,
      "text": "About a hundred milliseconds after the image comes on,"
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 128585.00000000001,
      "end_time": 131213.0,
      "text": "we see a positive bump in all four cases,"
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 131237.0,
      "end_time": 134250.0,
      "text": "and we call this the P100, and what we think that is"
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 134500.0,
      "end_time": 137125.0,
      "text": "is what happens in your brain when you recognize an object."
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 137149.0,
      "end_time": 139235.0,
      "text": "But damn, look at that signal for the face."
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 139259.0,
      "end_time": 140970.0,
      "text": "It looks different than the others."
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 140994.0,
      "end_time": 143884.0,
      "text": "There&#39;s a negative dip about 170 milliseconds"
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 143908.0,
      "end_time": 145447.0,
      "text": "after the image comes on."
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 145472.0,
      "end_time": 147222.0,
      "text": "What could be going on here?"
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 147246.0,
      "end_time": 150486.0,
      "text": "Research shows that our brain has a lot of neurons that are dedicated"
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 150510.0,
      "end_time": 151969.0,
      "text": "to recognizing human faces,"
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 151993.0,
      "end_time": 154837.0,
      "text": "so this N170 spike could be all those neurons"
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 154861.0,
      "end_time": 156846.0,
      "text": "firing at once in the same location,"
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 156870.0,
      "end_time": 158504.0,
      "text": "and we can detect that in the EEG."
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 159830.0,
      "end_time": 160903.0,
      "text": "So there are two takeaways here."
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 160927.0,
      "end_time": 164120.0,
      "text": "One, our eyes can&#39;t really detect the differences in patterns"
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 164360.0,
      "end_time": 165607.0,
      "text": "without averaging out the noise,"
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 165631.0,
      "end_time": 167868.0,
      "text": "and two, even after removing the noise,"
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 167892.0,
      "end_time": 170893.0,
      "text": "our eyes can only pick up the signals associated with faces."
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 170917.0,
      "end_time": 173185.0,
      "text": "So this is where we turn to machine learning."
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 173209.0,
      "end_time": 177185.0,
      "text": "Now, our eyes are not very good at picking up patterns in noisy data,"
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 177209.0,
      "end_time": 180155.0,
      "text": "but machine learning algorithms are designed to do just that,"
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 180179.0,
      "end_time": 183380.0,
      "text": "so could we take a lot of pictures and a lot of data"
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 183404.0,
      "end_time": 185194.0,
      "text": "and feed it in and train a computer"
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 185218.0,
      "end_time": 188599.0,
      "text": "to be able to interpret what Christy is looking at in real time?"
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 189880.0,
      "end_time": 193204.0,
      "text": "We&#39;re trying to code the information that&#39;s coming out of her EEG"
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 193229.0,
      "end_time": 194404.0,
      "text": "in real time"
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 194428.0,
      "end_time": 196889.0,
      "text": "and predict what it is that her eyes are looking at."
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 196913.0,
      "end_time": 198640.0,
      "text": "And if it works, what we should see"
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 198664.0,
      "end_time": 201450.0,
      "text": "is every time that she gets a picture of scenery,"
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 201690.0,
      "end_time": 203355.0,
      "text": "it should say scenery, scenery, scenery, scenery."
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 203379.0,
      "end_time": 205335.0,
      "text": "A face -- face, face, face, face,"
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 205360.0,
      "end_time": 208891.0,
      "text": "but it&#39;s not quite working that way, is what we&#39;re discovering."
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 213385.0,
      "end_time": 216933.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 216957.0,
      "end_time": 218108.0,
      "text": "OK."
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 218132.0,
      "end_time": 221514.0,
      "text": "Director: So what&#39;s going on here? GG: We need a new career, I think."
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 221538.0,
      "end_time": 222608.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 222632.0,
      "end_time": 225760.0,
      "text": "OK, so that was a massive failure."
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "start_time": 225100.0,
      "end_time": 228311.0,
      "text": "But we&#39;re still curious: How far could we push this technology?"
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "start_time": 228336.0,
      "end_time": 229976.0,
      "text": "And we looked back at what we did."
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "start_time": 230000.0,
      "end_time": 233143.0,
      "text": "We noticed that the data was coming into our computer very quickly,"
    },
    {
      "index": 91,
      "start_time": 233167.0,
      "end_time": 235408.0,
      "text": "without any timing of when the images came on,"
    },
    {
      "index": 92,
      "start_time": 235432.0,
      "end_time": 238308.0,
      "text": "and that&#39;s the equivalent of reading a very long sentence"
    },
    {
      "index": 93,
      "start_time": 238332.0,
      "end_time": 239936.0,
      "text": "without spaces between the words."
    },
    {
      "index": 94,
      "start_time": 239961.0,
      "end_time": 241399.0,
      "text": "It would be hard to read,"
    },
    {
      "index": 95,
      "start_time": 241423.0,
      "end_time": 245136.0,
      "text": "but once we add the spaces, individual words appear"
    },
    {
      "index": 96,
      "start_time": 245160.0,
      "end_time": 247204.0,
      "text": "and it becomes a lot more understandable."
    },
    {
      "index": 97,
      "start_time": 247228.0,
      "end_time": 249750.0,
      "text": "But what if we cheat a little bit?"
    },
    {
      "index": 98,
      "start_time": 249990.0,
      "end_time": 252636.0,
      "text": "By using a sensor, we can tell the computer when the image first appears."
    },
    {
      "index": 99,
      "start_time": 252660.0,
      "end_time": 256262.0,
      "text": "That way, the brainwave stops being a continuous stream of information,"
    },
    {
      "index": 100,
      "start_time": 256286.0,
      "end_time": 258997.0,
      "text": "and instead becomes individual packets of meaning."
    },
    {
      "index": 101,
      "start_time": 259209.99999999997,
      "end_time": 261388.99999999997,
      "text": "Also, we&#39;re going to cheat a little bit more,"
    },
    {
      "index": 102,
      "start_time": 261413.0,
      "end_time": 263225.0,
      "text": "by limiting the categories to two."
    },
    {
      "index": 103,
      "start_time": 263249.0,
      "end_time": 265632.0,
      "text": "Let&#39;s see if we can do some real-time mind-reading."
    },
    {
      "index": 104,
      "start_time": 265656.0,
      "end_time": 266891.0,
      "text": "In this new experiment,"
    },
    {
      "index": 105,
      "start_time": 266915.0,
      "end_time": 269120.0,
      "text": "we&#39;re going to constrict it a little bit more"
    },
    {
      "index": 106,
      "start_time": 269360.0,
      "end_time": 271288.0,
      "text": "so that we know the onset of the image"
    },
    {
      "index": 107,
      "start_time": 271312.0,
      "end_time": 274694.0,
      "text": "and we&#39;re going to limit the categories to \"face\" or \"scenery.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 108,
      "start_time": 275970.0,
      "end_time": 276608.0,
      "text": "Nathan: Face. Correct."
    },
    {
      "index": 109,
      "start_time": 277780.0,
      "end_time": 279131.0,
      "text": "Scenery. Correct."
    },
    {
      "index": 110,
      "start_time": 280251.0,
      "end_time": 282623.0,
      "text": "GG: So right now, every time the image comes on,"
    },
    {
      "index": 111,
      "start_time": 282648.0,
      "end_time": 284914.0,
      "text": "we&#39;re taking a picture of the onset of the image"
    },
    {
      "index": 112,
      "start_time": 284938.0,
      "end_time": 286633.0,
      "text": "and decoding the EEG."
    },
    {
      "index": 113,
      "start_time": 286657.0,
      "end_time": 287912.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s getting correct."
    },
    {
      "index": 114,
      "start_time": 287937.0,
      "end_time": 289516.0,
      "text": "Nathan: Yes. Face. Correct."
    },
    {
      "index": 115,
      "start_time": 289540.0,
      "end_time": 292399.0,
      "text": "GG: So there is information in the EEG signal, which is cool."
    },
    {
      "index": 116,
      "start_time": 292423.0,
      "end_time": 294960.0,
      "text": "We just had to align it to the onset of the image."
    },
    {
      "index": 117,
      "start_time": 295307.0,
      "end_time": 296618.0,
      "text": "Nathan: Scenery. Correct."
    },
    {
      "index": 118,
      "start_time": 299344.0,
      "end_time": 300494.0,
      "text": "Face. Yeah."
    },
    {
      "index": 119,
      "start_time": 300518.0,
      "end_time": 302806.0,
      "text": "GG: This means there is some information there,"
    },
    {
      "index": 120,
      "start_time": 302830.0,
      "end_time": 305743.0,
      "text": "so if we know at what time the picture came on,"
    },
    {
      "index": 121,
      "start_time": 305767.0,
      "end_time": 307766.0,
      "text": "we can tell what type of picture it was,"
    },
    {
      "index": 122,
      "start_time": 307790.0,
      "end_time": 312886.0,
      "text": "possibly, at least on average, by looking at these evoked potentials."
    },
    {
      "index": 123,
      "start_time": 312910.0,
      "end_time": 314235.0,
      "text": "Nathan: Exactly."
    },
    {
      "index": 124,
      "start_time": 314259.0,
      "end_time": 317780.0,
      "text": "GG: If you had told me at the beginning of this project this was possible,"
    },
    {
      "index": 125,
      "start_time": 317804.0,
      "end_time": 319540.0,
      "text": "I would have said no way."
    },
    {
      "index": 126,
      "start_time": 319790.0,
      "end_time": 321790.0,
      "text": "I literally did not think we could do this."
    },
    {
      "index": 127,
      "start_time": 321103.0,
      "end_time": 323169.0,
      "text": "Did our mind-reading experiment really work?"
    },
    {
      "index": 128,
      "start_time": 323193.0,
      "end_time": 325168.0,
      "text": "Yes, but we had to do a lot of cheating."
    },
    {
      "index": 129,
      "start_time": 325192.0,
      "end_time": 328970.0,
      "text": "It turns out you can find some interesting things in the EEG,"
    },
    {
      "index": 130,
      "start_time": 328121.0,
      "end_time": 330411.0,
      "text": "for example if you&#39;re looking at someone&#39;s face,"
    },
    {
      "index": 131,
      "start_time": 330435.0,
      "end_time": 332592.0,
      "text": "but it does have a lot of limitations."
    },
    {
      "index": 132,
      "start_time": 332616.0,
      "end_time": 335562.0,
      "text": "Perhaps advances in machine learning will make huge strides,"
    },
    {
      "index": 133,
      "start_time": 335586.0,
      "end_time": 338976.0,
      "text": "and one day we will be able to decode what&#39;s going on in our thoughts."
    },
    {
      "index": 134,
      "start_time": 339000.0,
